\f1\b What Helios Actually Is
\f0\b0                                                        \
                                                                                \
  A 
\f1\b 14B-parameter Diffusion Transformer
\f0\b0  that produces an infinite, steerable    \
  video stream. Key mechanics that matter for StudioYou:                        \
                                                                                \
  - 
\f1\b 33 frames per chunk
\f0\b0  (~1.4s at 24fps) \'97 commands queue for the next chunk, so\
   UI reactions to user actions appear within ~1-2 seconds  \
  - 
\f1\b Image-to-video
\f0\b0  \'97 upload any image, it animates it into a living scene; swap \
  mid-stream with \cf3 "blend"\cf2  transition                                            \
  - 
\f1\b \cf3 schedule_prompt\cf2  at specific chunks
\f0\b0  \'97 you can script a cinematic sequence in\
  advance, precisely timed                                                      \
  - 
\f1\b \cf3 set_seed
\f0\b0 \cf2  \'97 same seed = same video, always. Reproducible per-user worlds\
  - 
\f1\b \cf3 prompt_switched\cf2  event
\f0\b0  \'97 exact notification when the video transitions, lets \
  you sync UI to video frame-perfectly                                          \
  - 
\f1\b \cf3 pause\cf2 /\cf3 resume
\f0\b0 \cf2  \'97 stop generation when not in view, resume without losing state\
                                                                                \
  This is not a clip generator. It's a 
\f1\b live, scriptable, reactive video 
\f0\b0         \
  
\f1\b environment.
\f0\b0                                                                   \
